My emacs configuration files. -*- mode: org mode: auto-fill -*-
#+STARTUP: showall

* Project Detection

  Project roots are detected by =project.el= using a combination of VC (git)
  and marker files.  The following marker files are recognised as project roots
  (see =project-vc-extra-root-markers= in =init.el=):

  - =.project= — explicit project root marker (preferred)
  - =pyproject.toml=, =Cargo.toml=, =*.cabal=, =package.json=, etc.

** Git Submodules as Independent Projects

   By default =project-try-vc= walks up the git hierarchy and resolves a
   submodule to its superproject root.  A custom finder
   =kb/project-try-dot-project= is added to =project-find-functions= (before
   =project-try-vc=) to short-circuit this: if the *immediate* git root of
   the current file contains a =.project= file, that root is used as the
   project root regardless of any enclosing superproject.

   To make a git submodule an independent Emacs project, place an empty
   =.project= file at its root:

   #+BEGIN_SRC sh
   touch <submodule-root>/.project
   #+END_SRC

   Optionally add it to the submodule's =.git/info/exclude= to keep it out of
   git status without committing it:

   #+BEGIN_SRC sh
   echo ".project" >> <submodule-root>/.git/info/exclude
   #+END_SRC

